<SECOND>PM-People-Zaccaro,0113</SECOND>
<DATELINE>RUTLAND, Vt. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Zaccaro </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, the son of former vice presidential candidate <PERSON> Geraldine </PERSON> <PERSON> Ferraro </PERSON>, is appealing his conviction for selling $ 25 worth of cocaine to an undercover officer. Attorneys for <PERSON> Zaccaro </PERSON> filed the brief notice in <ORGANIZATION> Vermont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Rutland </LOCATION> on Thursday, indicating an appeal of both <PERSON> Zaccaro </PERSON>'s conviction and sentence, said Court Clerk <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Dingler </PERSON>. The case now goes to the <ORGANIZATION> Vermont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> for final review. <PERSON> Zaccaro </PERSON>, 24, has already begun serving his four-month sentence under a special house arrest program. The former <ORGANIZATION> Middlebury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> student was convicted in April by a jury of selling the drug to former Trooper <PERSON> Laura </PERSON> <PERSON> Manning </PERSON>.
