<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Homeless people and their advocates occupied houses, pitched tent cities and marched through streets demanding `` Housing Now'' as they sought to rally support across the nation. At least 78 people were arrested. `` We've made a strong statement that homeless people are going to get off their knees and fight for their rights,'' said <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Flagg </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arizona </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION> for the Homeless, minutes before he and 10 others were arrested Thursday while occupying a vacant townhouse in <LOCATION> Tucson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ariz. </LOCATION>. Voter registration drives also were a part of Homeless Action Day, a protest that organizers said involved at least 60 cities nationwide `` I'm not really all that far out of the mud, but I can still see a little bit better than some of these people,'' said <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Dized </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, construction worker who said he used to be homeless. `` I'd be less than I am if I did n't support this. I've been through it; I know what it's like to want a home. In <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, two policemen and a demonstrator were injured in a fight that erupted after demonstrators tried to occupy a boarded-up <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Redevelopment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> building. Some of the 75 people who marched on behalf of the homeless used crowbars to pry boards off the building, and when police tried to stop them, they swung the boards at the officers, police spokesman <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Santry </PERSON> said. Eighteen people were arrested, including one who was charged with disorderly conduct and possession of a dangerous weapon. Three others were charged with assault and battery on a police officer. Thirty-s