are the blame. `` Though it's easy to blame the Republicans, the Democrats are just as responsible for the situation that exists,'' said <PERSON> Keith </PERSON> <PERSON> Summa </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION> for the Homeless in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, the homeless occupied 13 empty government-owned homes, demanding ownership of the houses and federal money to rehabilitate them. Fifty homeless people and supporters in <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, marched in 90-degree weather, carrying signs bearing such messages as `` Street people are people.'' <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>'s homeless joined their counterparts nationwide by erecting tent cities and filing a lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> Newark </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION>, accusing it of demolishing low-income units without replacing them, contrary to federal law. About 100 people demonstrated at <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hall </LOCATION> in support of the class-action lawsuit filed Thursday in state <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, said <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Burgess </PERSON>, a leader of the <ORGANIZATION> Newark </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Low-Income </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION>. Housing Authority Executive Director <PERSON> Milton </PERSON> <PERSON> Buck </PERSON> denied <PERSON> Burgess </PERSON>' charges and said the authority would fight the lawsuit In <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.M. </LOCATION>, seven homeless people and 45 supporters rallied at a park Thursday night, then marched two blocks c