pute this. `` I return my telephone calls,'' <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said in a recent interview. There had been speculation that <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> would be staying at a cabin near Cody, <LOCATION> Wyo. </LOCATION>, on the South Fork of the <LOCATION> Shoshone </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> owned by Sen. <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Simpson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Wyo </LOCATION>., a close friend of <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s and among those mentioned as a possible running mate However, <PERSON> Simpson </PERSON> spokeswoman <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Kay </PERSON> <PERSON> Hill </PERSON> said Friday that the vice president would not be staying there and that <PERSON> Simpson </PERSON> had no plans to join the fishing trip. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> will reappear on Wednesday, the next-to-last night of the Democratic convention, with two campaign apperances planned in the the <LOCATION> Detroit </LOCATION> area. And on Thursday, the day when <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> will deliver his acceptance speech, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> dips into the South with campaign events planned in <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Greenville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION>. That will break a longstanding tradition in which presidential contenders have ceased political activity during the rival party's nominating <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> plans to campaign in <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> the following day and in <LOCATION> Tennessee </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> July 23. He will address a business and professional womens' convention in <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.M. </LOCATION>, on July 24.
