<HEAD>DA: Racial Motivation In Murder A Serious Concern</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents beginning with 9th graf.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By LESLIE ZGANJAR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The murder of a 19-year-old black woman whose body was found with `` KKK'' carved on her leg is being investigated as possibly racially motivated, a prosecutor said Friday. District Attorney <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Kavanagh </PERSON> said he talked with Gov. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> about the case Friday and <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> had pledged `` full support of state resources'' to help with the case. <PERSON> Anna </PERSON> <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON>, 19, was found dead Tuesday, but information about the letters on her leg were not released until Thursday. The letters were written with a sharp instrument, said <PERSON> Kavanagh </PERSON>, who refused to comment on many aspects of the investigation. `` As far as racial involvement, we are concerned,'' <PERSON> Kavanagh </PERSON> said. `` We are concerned.'' Preliminary autopsy results indicated Miss <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON> was strangled and struck on the head with a blunt instrument, police said. A bite on the neck and other marks also were found on her body. Miss <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON> had last been seen Monday evening at the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grill </ORGANIZATION>, a few doors down from the alleyway where her blood-stained sweatsuit was found. Her partly clothed body was found another block away. While <PERSON> Kavanagh </PERSON> would n't comment on reports that Miss <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON> was a drug addict, the woman's father told the <ORGANIZATION> Kingston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Freeman </ORGANIZATION> that his daughter had fallen victim to drugs. `` I'm almost positive it was a drug rub,'' <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON> told the newspaper. The only arrest in the case came Wednesday, when a man police described as a transient was charged with engaging in sexual contact with <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Kithcart </PERSON>'s corpse. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Kiernan </PE