<BYLINE>By SCOTT SONNER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Massive thunderstorms packing tornadoes and wind gusts up to 92 mph slammed into <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bluffs </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, on Friday, injuring at least 40 people and damaging more than 100 homes. One tornado uprooted trees, downed power lines, started fires and overturned railroad cars in a 2-mile stretch in western Council Bluffs along Interstate 29 and the <LOCATION> Missouri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, which divides the two cities. Most of Council Bluffs' 60,000 residents were without power Friday night and the situation was not expected to change through morning, said <PERSON> Matt </PERSON> <PERSON> Daunis </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Iowa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Power </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Light </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Council Bluffs Mayor <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanafan </PERSON> ordered a curfew from 10 p.m. to dawn to guard against looting Members of the <ORGANIZATION> Iowa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> patroled the streets. An <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION> man was reported in critical condition with neck and possible internal injuries after a tree crashed onto the roof of his car. Most other injuries were minor, said officials of three hospitals who counted a total of 40 people treated for storm-related injuries. Exits off Interstate 29 into Council Bluffs were closed and the <ORGANIZATION> Iowa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> sealed off the area most heavily damaged. Possible tornadoes and funnel clouds were reported throughout the <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION> area as hail fell and more than 2 inches of rain caused street flooding. `` We went to the hallway and we were praying very hard,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGAN