<HEAD>Social Service Agency Delays Needle Exchange</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB BAUM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Insurance problems will delay a plan aimed at reducing the spread of AIDS by distributing free needles to intravenous drug users, a social service agency official said Thursday. <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON>, executive director of the agency Outside In, said her organization hopes to begin giving out the hypodermic needles by late August. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> said the insurance company, <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paul </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paul </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, is concerned about the agency's liability because the project, which was scheduled to begin this month, is unprecedented in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. `` It is difficult to assess the exposure and risk, and therefore it's difficult to determine rates,'' she said. <PERSON> Beth </PERSON> <PERSON> Murray </PERSON>, spokeswoman for <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paul </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION>, said the company notified Outside In that the project was n't covered under its existing policy. `` It takes us into areas of unknown liability,'' she said. `` We're especially concerned for the potential of the spread of AIDS from needles supplied by the clinic and later re-used.'' Under the yearlong project, 125 drug abusers will exchange used needles for new ones and receive counseling. The project is financed by a $ 67,000 grant from the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> for AIDS Research. If the insurance cost increases greatly, <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> said, she is confident that more funds can be obtained because of the interest in the experiment nationwide. <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON>, the largest medical liability insurer in the country, has provided comprehensive medical malpractice and liability insurance to Outside In for 10 years. The agency never has had a claim filed against its policy. `` We're negotiating with them to work this out,'' <PERSON> Murray </PERSON> said. `` They've been insured with our company for several years and it's important for us to work it out with them. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> said the company's action came as a surprise because the problems did n't surface when agency officials spoke with the insurance company about the proposed project a year ago and again when the financing was obtained earlier this year. She said the company apparently became concerned after news accounts of the project were published. Outside In learned about the problem about two weeks ago, she said. Acquired immune deficiency syndrome is most often spread through sexual contact, sharing of needles by intravenous drug abusers, or by transfusions of blood or blood products, experts say.
