the automatic transmission. In addition to the almost $ 2.2 million award to Mrs. <PERSON> Rose </PERSON>, the jury awarded her husband, <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON>, $ 700,000 for his suffering. Mrs. <PERSON> Rose </PERSON> suffered a broken neck, brain damage and bladder problems and has incurred medical expenses of more than $ 500,000, her lawyers said. The jury found <ORGANIZATION> Volkwagen </ORGANIZATION> innocent of malice despite the design defect, ruling the company did not deliberately disregard the rights and safety of others. The Audi 5000 has been recalled twice before: In 1982 to raise the height of the brake pedal so the brakes will work even if the driver steps on the brake and accelerator pedal at the same time; and in 1981 to anchor floor carpets so they could n't slide up over the accelerator and keep it from rising when the driver's foot is removed.
